news.title: Extension work of Jaipur Metro to begin soon, says Rajasthan CM
news.para: “I know that Line 1 of Jaipur Metro needs to be extended. Soon the extension work will get started,” said Ashok Gehlot during a programme of Rajasthan Housing Board on Friday.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh showcases housing program on national platform
news.para: According to officials, the 30 lakh houses will come up on 71,811 acres distributed to the beneficiaries in Andhra Pradesh. The state government is spending about Rs.3,525 crore on layout development and Rs 32,900 crore on infrastructure creation.

news.title: Tidco houses handed over to 5,000 beneficiaries in Visakhapatnam
news.para: The GVMC has identified 24,192 eligible beneficiaries for Tidco houses. While 22,936 houses are being constructed in the suburbs, 1,256 houses are coming up in various slums in the city.

news.title: Kanpur development body gives allotment letters of plots under various schemes
news.para: KDA had launched an E-auction project for plots of different schemes for different classes between August 5 and September 21.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body issues notices to 3,200 property tax defaulters
news.para: As per the records of the MC, around 1,900 tax defaulters have been identified from residential category, while the rest around 1,300 defaulters fall in commercial category.

news.title: SC extends interim bail granted to ex-CMD, ex-director of Amrapali Group
news.para: The bench allowed him to visit a hospital in Chennai for the surgery and said he will have to file a report about his medical condition five days after the procedure.

news.title: PMAY has become major medium for ushering in socio-economic change: Prime Minister
news.para: In Madhya Pradesh, about 30 lakh houses have been built under the PMAY in the last eight years and another 9-10 lakh houses are being constructed, PM said.

news.title: No immediate plan to launch REIT: DLF
news.para: "There is no change in the plan or the direction and I think both GIC and we are reasonably committed to the entire thing, but given the high interest rate scenario currently going on and the overall uncertainty, this obviously is not the best time for a new REIT," DLF CEO Ashok Tyagi told investors.

news.title: Telangana HC quashes CBI's case on India Cements
news.para: The case of the CBI in this chargesheet was that there was a quid pro quo arrangement between India Cements MD N Srinivasan and then Andhra Pradesh chief minister YS Rajasekhara Reddy’s son YS Jagan Mohan Reddy.

news.title: Bihar to distribute 1.6 lakh acres of Bhoodan land
news.para: "Around 1.60 lakh hectares of clear and hassle-free Bhoodan land have been identified, and accordingly, will be available for distribution among the landless people. The distribution will start after December," revenue and land reforms minister Alok Kumar Mehta said on Friday.

news.title: RLDA seeks bids for development of nine multi-functional complexes in four states
news.para: ​The nine sites that are proposed to be given on a 45-year lease for the development of multifunctional complexes (MFCs) have a total plot area of approximately 10,009 square metres.

news.title: PWD to implement measures to curb construction debris: Goa PWD minister
news.para: He said that once the plant proposed to handle construction and demolition waste comes up in the state, the issue of illegal dumping of debris will find a permanent solution.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC directs state govt to place changes made to CRDA Act before them
news.para: The high court earlier stayed the GO issued by the state government to allot house sites in Amaravati to people from other areas. The high court held that allotting house sites to others in capital regions is in violation of zonal regulation plan and CRDA master plan.

news.title: Panjab University, Chandigarh civic body officials to discuss property tax issue
news.para: Sources in the civic body authority said that PU had raised the matter with senior officers of the Chandigarh administration and the MC conducted a fresh survey.

news.title: HC expresses concerns over illegal constructions in Lucknow
news.para: ​The bench directed the LDA to furnish a list of such officials who maintain calculated silence and turn a blind eye when illegal constructions come up. It further directed the authority to submit an action-taken report against the erring officials.
